  "response": "```dockerfile
# Stage 1: chef
FROM rust:1.78-bookworm AS chef
WORKDIR /app
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
COPY . .
RUN cargo chef prepare --recipe-path recipe.json

# Stage 2: rust-builder
FROM rust:1.78-bookworm AS rust-builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-dev && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
COPY --from=chef /app/recipe.json recipe.json
RUN cargo chef cook --release --recipe-path recipe.json
COPY . .
RUN cargo build --release

# Stage 3: python-builder
FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm AS python-builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir transformers tokenizers safetensors

# Stage 4: runtime
FROM debian:bookworm-slim AS runtime
LABEL maintainer="ml-team" \
      description="Rust + Python ML inference server" \
      version="1.0"

WORKDIR /app

RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    curl \
    python3 \
    libpython3.11 \
    ca-certificates && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/* && \
    groupadd -g 1000 inference && \
    useradd -u 1000 -g inference -m -s /bin/bash inference

COPY --from=python-builder --chown=inference:inference /opt/venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH" \
    VIRTUAL_ENV="/opt/venv"

COPY --from=rust-builder --chown=inference:inference /app/target/release/inference-server /usr/local/bin/inference-server

USER inference

EXPOSE 8080

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
    CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

CMD ["/usr/local/bin/inference-server", "--port", "8080"]
```",
